"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-newslens-2024-0208-1431267-paris-olympics-medals\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Medallists at the Paris Olympics will be rewarded with a piece of the Eiffel Tower, organisers have said, as they unveiled the hexagon-shaped medals forged out of scrap metal from the monument.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea was to link the games with symbols of France, said Thierry Reboul, creative director of Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990191270500441, \"rank\": 0.0009093612067164208, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7629042340858768e-16, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}, {\"begin\": 292, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999994106474, \"rank\": 5.894343689425365e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The absolute symbol of Paris and France is the Eiffel Tower,\\\" said Mr Reboul.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.342984194350423e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 339, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990191270500441, \"rank\": 0.0009093612067164208, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's the opportunity for the athletes to bring back a piece of Paris with them.\\\"\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 449, \"end\": 454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.342984194350423e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Designed by jeweller Chaumet, the 18-gram hexagon tokens, representing the shape of France, are made of iron from past refurbishments of the Tower stored for years in a warehouse whose location is secret.\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990191270500441, \"rank\": 0.0009093612067164208, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They sit in the centre of the gold, silver and bronze medals, ringed with grooves evoking light rays bursting outward - drawn from a tiara design in Chaumet's archives.\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chaumet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chaumet\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chaumet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chaumet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The back of the medals features the Greek goddess of victory, Nike, charging forward, with the Acropolis to one side and the Eiffel Tower to the other.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.894514265896589, \"rank\": 0.049637425405028364, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"score\": 0.9851865610578406, \"rank\": 0.015033413495881718, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\"}, {\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9531544117169947, \"rank\": 0.04914316685030178, \"text\": \"Acropolis\", \"types\": [\"Q9259\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_of_Athens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paralympics medals feature a view of the Eiffel Tower from underneath, and are stamped with Paris 2024 in braille - homage to the Frenchman who invented it.\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1089, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999994106474, \"rank\": 5.894343689425365e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 5,084 medals are produced by France's mint, the Monnaie de Paris.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1188, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990191270500441, \"rank\": 0.0009093612067164208, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, 